title: DWU's Fitts Takes GPAC Golfer-Of-The-Week
text:
DWU's Fitts Takes GPAC Golfer-Of-The-Week POSTED: 11:59 AM CDT Oct 08, 2015 Large Text MITCHELL, S.D. - 
After winning the first two Great Plains Athletic Conference Qualifiers of the season, Dakota Wesleyan University senior Lauren Fitts picked up a weekly conference honor to add to her impressive list of accomplishments. More from KDLT Indictment: Doctor Falsely Reported Wedding Expenses To IRS 
Fitts, a Brookings, S.D., native, was named the Great Plains Athletic Conference Women’s Golfer of the Week, the conference announced Wednesday night. The honor is her first of 2015-16 after taking home three straight in the spring of her junior season. 
In the first qualifier on Sept. 30 in Sioux City, Iowa, Fitts lapped the field with a 75, eight strokes better than the rest of the GPAC golfers. In pursuit of her four-straight GPAC title, Fitts extended her lead in the conference race to 11 strokes with a second win in less than a week Monday at Southern Hills Golf Course in Hastings, Neb. 
The push by Fitts helped the Tigers climb from a fourth-place tie after the opening round into a tie for second, just 10 strokes off the pace. Copyright © 2015, KDLT. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
